  "description": "Thomas Aquinas (c. 1225-1274) was a Dominican friar and theologian whose Summa Theologiae is the canonical synthesis of Aristotelian philosophy with Christian theology, and whose articulation of the virtues, vices, and pastoral apparatus of the soul is the upstream institutional grammar that cybernetic postliberalism treats as the prior form of californication.",
